BUILDER'S & MECHANIC'S LIEN CONTRACT
(With Transfer of Lien)
This Builder's & Mechanic's Lien Contract ("Construction Contract") for improvements
is made on the 23rd day of FEBRUARY, 2022, between WILLIAM MARK BLUMENSHINE
(WHO ACQUIRED TITLE AS W. MARK BLUMENSHINE) AND DONNA JEAN
BLUMENSHINE (WHO ACQUIRED TITLE AS DONNA J. BLUMENSHINE), HUSBAND
AND WIFE ("Owner")and TOSCANA HOMES AND PROPERTIES LLC ("Contractor"), and
provides for a Transfer of Lien to Zions Bancorporation, N.A. dba Amegy Bank ("Lender").
1. Construction of Improvements. Contractor agrees to furnish the necessary materials
and labor-and-to complete the construction on the property in a good, workmanlike
manner according to plans and specifications agreed on by Owner and Contractor.
2. Description of Property. The Improvements shall be constructed upon the following
property:
BEING LOT TEN (19), PHASE FIVE (5), SECTION TWO (2), BARTON
CREEK LAKESIDE, A SUBDIVISION LOCATED IN BURNET AND TRAVIS
COUNTIES, TEXAS, AS SHOWN BY PLAT RECORDED IN CABINET 2,
SLIDE 134C-134D, PLAT RECORDS OF BURNET COUNTY, TEXAS. (THIS
LOT LIES IN BOTH BURNET AND TRAVIS COUNTY)
3. Contract Sum. Owner agrees to pay or
ay, or cause to be paid, to Contractor for the
construction of the improvements, the Contract Sum of $1,495,691.00.
4. Note Payable to Lender. In consideration of the agreement by Lender to advance funds
pursuant to a Construction Loan Agreement executed of even date herewith among
Owner and Lender and acknowledged by Contractor, \Owner, has executed and
delivered to Lender a note ("Note") in the sum of $1,223,000.00, to be advanced by
Lender in accordance with the Construction, Loan Agreement. The Note shall be
secured by a partial or full transfer to Lender of the lien created by this Construction
Contract and shall also be secured by a Deed of Trust executed by Owner that renews
and extends the lien created by this Construction Contract, and provides for a non-
judicial foreclosure in the event of default.
5. Lien to Secure Note. To secure the payment of the Contract Sum by Owner to
Contractor, Owner gives and grants to Contractor, a lien as provided by the
constitution and laws of the State of Texas on the above-described property; together
with all the improvements now or later constructed on the property and all casements,
rights, and appurtenances, all of which shall be deemed to be and remain a part of the
property covered by this Construction Contract.
